<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="114" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Pitheciidae" genus="Callicebus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Callicebus barbarabrownae" order="Primates" pageId="9" pageNumber="114" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barbarabrownae">Callicebus barbarabrownae</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Caatinga, and has been recorded in the Brazilian states of Bahia and Sergipe (
<bibRefCitation pageId="9" pageNumber="114">Hershkovitz 1990b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Marinho Filho, J" pageId="36" pageNumber="141" url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02381883" year="1997">
Marinho-Filho and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="VerÃ­ssimo">Verissimo</normalizedToken>
1997
